08/05/2006
MITROVICA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Unknown gunmen opened fire on a vehicle belonging to the Rasko-Prizren Eparchy of the Serbian Orthodox Church in Kosovo on Saturday (6 May) evening. 
According to media reports, the incident happened on a road near Mitrovica leading to the Sokolic monastery, in an area populated mainly by ethnic Albanians. 
The car was carrying a Serb priest, his wife, and their young children, aged 6 months and 3 years. 
There were no injuries. 
The incident was reported to the Kosovo police. 
(RTS, Tanjug - 07/05/06)
